## Rendering Patterns

### Fixed Items (Dashboard)
Fixed items render inline without drag-and-drop wrapper:

```tsx
<li key={item.path}>
  <Link to={item.path} className="...">
    {/* Icon */}
    <span className="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-lg">
      {item.icon}
    </span>

    {/* Label */}
    <span className="flex-1 text-base leading-5 font-medium truncate">
      {item.label}
    </span>

    {/* Settings button (if hasSettings) */}
    {item.hasSettings && (
      <button className="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
        <span className="text-sm">⚙</span>
      </button>
    )}

    {/* Expand/collapse button (if children) */}
    {hasChildren && (
      <button className="w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
        <span className={`text-xs ${expanded ? 'rotate-90' : ''}`}>▶</span>
      </button>
    )}
  </Link>
</li>
```

### Draggable Items (Schedule, Notes, Tasks)
Draggable items use `SortableNavItem` component with `@dnd-kit`:

```tsx
const SortableNavItem = ({ item, isCollapsed, isActive }) => {
  const { attributes, listeners, setNodeRef, transform, transition } = useSortable({
    id: item.path
  });

  return (
    <li
      ref={setNodeRef}
      style={{ transform, transition }}
      {...attributes}
      {...listeners}
      className="cursor-grab active:cursor-grabbing"
    >
      <Link to={item.path} className="...">
        {/* Same structure as fixed items */}
      </Link>
    </li>
  );
};
```

**Key Difference:** Drag listeners are on the `<li>` element, not a separate handle.

