## Sub-Pages (Children)

### When to Use
Add children when a top-level page has multiple distinct views/sections:
- Schedule → Timer, Entries, Summary, Calendar, Projects
- Notes → Graph, Diagrams, Forms

### Pattern
```tsx
{hasChildren && expanded && !isCollapsed && (
  <ul className="ml-6 mt-1 space-y-1">
    {item.children!.map((child) => (
      <li key={child.path}>
        <Link to={child.path} className="...">
          {/* Smaller icon (w-4 h-4) */}
          <span className="w-4 h-4 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm">
            {child.icon}
          </span>
          {/* Smaller label (text-sm) */}
          <span className="flex-1 text-sm leading-5 font-medium truncate">
            {child.label}
          </span>
        </Link>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>
)}
```

