## Adding a New Navigation Item

### Checklist

#### 1. Decide: Fixed or Draggable?
- **Fixed:** Only if it should always be first (like Dashboard)
- **Draggable:** For all other top-level pages

#### 2. Add to Navigation Array
```typescript
// For draggable items (most common)
const draggableNavigation: NavItem[] = [
  // ... existing items
  {
    icon: '🆕',
    label: 'New Feature',
    path: '/new-feature',
    shortcut: 'F',
    hasSettings: false,
    children: [], // Optional
  },
];
```

#### 3. Update Store Default Order
If adding a draggable item, update `useSidebarNavStore.ts`:

```typescript
const DEFAULT_NAV_ORDER = ['/schedule', '/notes', '/tasks', '/new-feature'];
```

#### 4. Test Checklist
- [ ] Icon displays correctly (20px size)
- [ ] Label truncates if too long
- [ ] Hover states work (background color change)
- [ ] Active state shows blue accent bar
- [ ] If draggable: can be reordered
- [ ] If draggable: order persists after refresh
- [ ] If has children: expand/collapse works
- [ ] If has children: button aligns with other expand buttons
- [ ] If has settings: gear icon appears on hover
- [ ] Works in collapsed sidebar mode
- [ ] Works in mobile drawer mode
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works

